The Africa Centres for Disease Control and Prevention (Africa CDC) has said that there are now 9,198 confirmed cases of Coronavirus (COVID-19) in 51 countries across Africa. The health agency stated this in a tweet on its official Twitter account on Monday morning. According to the tweet, COVID-19 had killed 414 people in Africa, while a total of 813 patients have recovered from the deadly disease across the continent. “#COVID19-UPDATE IN AFRICA: 6 APRIL 2020 – 9:00 am EAT. “51@_AfricanUnion member states reporting 9,198 COVID-19 cases, 414 deaths, and 813 recoveries by region,” it said. DAILY POST recalls that Africa CDC had provided an update on Coronavirus on Sunday morning.